# Trivy config (IaC misconfig) ignore list — W4.
#
# These are SANCTIONED ADR deviations, NOT unhandled risk. conftest
# (deploy/kubernetes/policy/rego/hardening.rego) is the AUTHORITATIVE,
# resource-scoped policy-as-test gate for each one: it asserts the deviation is
# present ONLY on the sanctioned workload and that every other workload stays
# subject to the hardened rule. Trivy's generic IaC checks cannot encode those
# ADR exceptions and would gate on the intentional deviation, so they are
# suppressed HERE for the `trivy config` (misconfig) scan ONLY. Image CVE scans
# (docker job) are a different finding type and are unaffected by this file.
#
# Each suppression below is mirrored by a stronger, scoped conftest rule.

# --- seccomp-installer DaemonSet (ADR-0031 §3/§5) ---
# The install-profile container MUST run as root with a writable host path to
# seed the kubelet Localhost seccomp profile directory
# (/var/lib/kubelet/seccomp/netops/) so the packet-analysis pod can start. The
# pause container is fully hardened; the hostPath is the single seccomp dir.
# Already object-annotated for kube-linter.
AVD-KSV-0014
KSV-0014
AVD-KSV-0118
KSV-0118

# --- packet-capture NET_RAW (ADR-0031 §1/§2) ---
# packet-capture legitimately adds NET_RAW for raw-socket capture. conftest's
# restrict-net-raw + net-raw-label assertions scope NET_RAW to packet-capture
# ALONE and prove packet-analysis (the parser) never carries it. A NET_RAW
# regression on any other workload still fails conftest.
AVD-KSV-0119
KSV-0119
